-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DERIVATIVE WORK NOTICE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This repository (https://github.com/FugginOld/aircraft-taxonomy-db) is a
derivative work of the upstream database maintained by the SDR-Enthusiasts
community at https://github.com/sdr-enthusiasts/plane-alert-db.

The underlying aircraft data (ICAO hex codes, registrations, operators, and
type designations) originates from the upstream project and is used here in
accordance with the Open Database License (ODbL v1.0). Under ODbL, this
derivative work must:
  1. Attribute the original database and its authors (done above).
  2. Keep derivative databases open under the same ODbL license.
  3. Keep the attribution and this notice intact in all copies or
     substantial uses of the database.

Differences introduced in this derivative work:
  - The original personality/group-based category scheme (~53 categories) has
    been replaced with a structured aviation-taxonomy scheme (~24 categories),
    classifying aircraft by mission type rather than by group membership or
    cultural association.
  - Aircraft records carry three structured tags: primary mission role,
    capability/configuration, and propulsion/airframe type.
  - Automated data-synchronisation tooling (scripts/, api/, cache/) has been
    added to keep aircraft metadata current against public canonical sources
    (OpenSky Network, FAA, ICAO).
  - A Privacy ICAO Address (PIA) sub-list and a separate aircraft-images list
    are not maintained in this derivative at this time.

These changes do not affect the authorship or attribution obligations described
above.
